      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"spooky\" feeling you're sensing is precisely what Einstein famously called \"spooky action at a distance.\" It's not just a feeling, though, it's a profound violation of our everyday, classical intuition, which is built on the idea that nothing can influence something else faster than the speed of light. This is where the logic of the mundane world breaks down, as if a tiny, hyper-efficient, and utterly unpredictable line of communication is running between the entangled particles. It's so weird, it's often described as non-local.",
